Variant 1 (Figure 93
A-C
) was collected in Sinaloa, Mexico. It is very similar to the type form except as follows: promesonotum more domed; pronotal dorsum strongly carinulate, without punctae.

Variant 4 (Figure 93
J-L
) is from another site in Oaxaca (10.6km N Jct 190/135). It varies from the type as follows: promesonotum in profile low-domed and appearing very long, with the anterior face sloping gently into the metanotal groove; pronotum with many longitudinal carinulae around humeri, and a few on dorsum; gastral pilosity longer.
